{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"53753847-edd6-42de-ad5b-2eab54f891c3","content":"Here's the recommended MSTest setup:\n\n## 1. Project file (`MyTests.csproj`)\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.7\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net9.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\nThat's it — `MSTest.Sdk` brings in the test framework, runner, and analyzers automatically. No need for explicit package references.\n\n## 2. Enable parallel execution\n\nAdd a file called `MyTests.csproj` already supports it, but you configure it via assembly attribute or `.runsettings`. The simplest approach — add to a global file like `Usings.cs`:\n\n```csharp\n[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.MethodLevel)]\n```\n\nThis runs all test methods in parallel by default.\n\n## 3. Make database tests run sequentially\n\nMark your database test class with `[DoNotParallelize]`:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Can_Insert_Record() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Can_Query_Records() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n**Summary:**\n\n| Concern | Mechanism |\n|---------|-----------|\n| Minimal project | `MSTest.Sdk` (replaces all boilerplate) |\n| Parallel by default | `[assembly: Parallelize]` |\n| Sequential for DB tests | `[DoNotParallelize]` on the class |\n\n`ExecutionScope.MethodLevel` gives maximum parallelism (methods across all classes run concurrently). Use `ClassLevel` if you want classes to run in parallel but methods within a class to be sequential.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c92dc2fc-435c-43cf-9029-dfe9974c24d5","outputTokens":438,"requestId":"5806:D3ED5:17220A9:189C6F8:6A033949"},"id":"062a6aea-75d5-42c8-80a1-00281817c2f6","timestamp":"2026-05-12T14:29:42.287Z","parentId":"10345cc7-6423-4064-9499-7a0550fe73f2"}
